^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 285 - February 25, 2002^*N 
 ^*BIOC Grand Prix Edition Number 3^*N 
 ^*BThe Canada-Italy Semi-Final^*N }
^-
This week's deal is the third part of my continuing account of the recent ^*BIOC Grand Prix^*N in Salt Lake City. If you have not done so already, I suggest that you read parts 1 and 2 of this series, available as ^*BDeals of the Week 283^*N and ^*B284^*N (February 11 and 18, 2002) through this web site. 

I hope you enjoy this week's deals!

^*BFred Gitelman
Bridge Base Inc.^*N
^*Hwww.bridgebase.com^*N

My Canadian Team (partner ^*BJoey Silver^*N and ^*BNick Gartaganis-Peter Jones^*N, ^*BKeith Balcombe^*N-^*BGord Campbell^*N) had unexpectedly finished 4th out of 10 strong teams after the robin robin phase of the 2002 IOC Grand Prix. We had thereby qualified for the semi-finals and would face Italy over 48 boards. The winner of this match would play the winner of the Norway-Poland semi-final for the Gold Medal. There were plenty of people betting on Italy, Norway, and Poland at this point. Nobody was betting on Canada, not even ^*BGeorge Mittelman^*N.

Our team had done well to get this far, but we were about to play a lot of boards against some of the best players in the world. Italy would enjoy a 6 IMP carryover (as they had demolished our team when we met in the round robin), but most people did not think they would need it.
