The only good news about the Italian team was that one of their key players, ^*BNorberto Bocchi^*N was not playing. His regular partner, ^*BGiorgio Duboin^*N would play with ^*BGuido Ferraro^*N, while ^*BAlfredo Versace^*N would play with both ^*BLorenzo Lauria^*N (his regular partner) and ^*BDano de Falco^*N. Although Italy was not quite at full strength, they still had 5 A-1 players on their team and one of the world's best partnerships in ^*BLauria^*N-^*BVersace^*N.

